18. Security Best Practices
Never expose passwords.
Store only encrypted passwords.
Use HTTPS in production.
Validate every JWT request.
Set appropriate token expiration.
Rotate refresh tokens after use.
Revoke tokens on logout.
Prevent brute-force attacks using rate limiting.
Validate email before activating accounts.


19. Definition of Done

The authentication foundation is complete when:

Registration API is available.
Login API returns valid JWT.
Refresh token flow works.
Passwords are encrypted.
Email verification is functional.
Protected APIs reject unauthorized requests.
Role-based authentication is configured.
Security configuration passes all tests.
